%% Sequence Diagram — Inference Request with Fallback
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Client (SDK)
    participant I as router-ingress
    participant Sec as router-security
    participant Core as router-core
    participant Cache as router-cache (Redis)
    participant P1 as provider-anthropic
    participant P2 as provider-openai
    participant K as Kafka

    C->>I: POST /v1/inference (policy, messages)
    I->>Sec: authenticate + authorize + rate-limit check
    Sec-->>I: OK (tenantId resolved)
    I->>Core: route(InferenceRequest)

    Core->>Core: resolve effective RoutingPolicy
    Core->>Cache: lookup(cacheKey)
    Cache-->>Core: miss

    Core->>Core: enumerate eligible candidates
    Core->>Cache: fetch live provider scores
    Cache-->>Core: scores (latency, error rate, cost, capacity)
    Core->>Core: RoutingStrategy.rank() → [anthropic, openai]

    Core->>P1: invoke(request)  %% attempt 1
    P1-->>Core: 503 Service Unavailable

    Note over Core: retryable failure, pre-first-byte → advance to next candidate

    Core->>P2: invoke(request)  %% attempt 2
    P2-->>Core: 200 OK (completion)

    Core->>Core: normalize response
    Core-->>I: InferenceResponse (routing trace: anthropic failed, openai succeeded)
    I-->>C: 200 OK

    Core-)K: emit usage/cost/latency event (async, off hot path)
    K-)Cache: async score update consumer refreshes provider scores
